International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 14 Sep 2006
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information, Vol. 19 - No. 37 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/A_CURRENT.HTM#Sec0>

CLASSICAL SWINE FEVER IN CROATIA: Follow-up report No. 2
------------------------------------------------------
Information received on 7 Sep 2006 from Dr Mate Brstilo, Director of
the Veterinary Administration, Ministry of Agriculture and Forestry, Zagreb:
End of this report period: 6 Sep 2006.
Identification of agent: classical swine fever virus.
Date of start of the event: 17 Jul 2006.
Clinical disease: yes.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, post-mortem and laboratory.
New outbreaks: 6 new outbreaks were reported in Osijecko-baranjska
county (Bijelo Brdo) and Vukovarsko srijemska (5 farms at Borovo)
between 14 and 28 Aug. There were a total of 578 susceptible pigs on
the 6 farms. Two farms in Borovo reported 6 and 3 cases each, all of
which died. The rest of the pigs were destroyed.
Description of affected population: domestic pigs in family-run farms.
Diagnosis: Laboratory where diagnostic tests were performed: Croatian
Veterinary Institute, Zagreb
Results: ELISA between 16 Aug and 1 Sep 2006 were positive
Source of outbreaks or origin of infection: contact with wild animals
suspected.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[This report includes more farms and pigs than in previous reports --
see reference below. All the farms are reported as small family-run
farms and contact with wild boar is suspected -- a not too surprising
source of transmission in this part of the world. - Mod.PC]
